No tissue samples,
but Greg was an organ donor.

587
00:30:17,129 --> 00:30:21,511
Transplant unit at Pennsylvania hospital
had some blood samples stored.

588
00:30:21,511 --> 00:30:23,843
- Lethal levels of digoxin.
- What's that?

589
00:30:23,843 --> 00:30:26,213
Medication used to stabilize
an irregular heart beat.

590
00:30:26,213 --> 00:30:28,098
And it can be deadly
if you want it to be.

591
00:30:28,098 --> 00:30:30,795
Overdose symptoms
are nausea, headache,

592
00:30:30,795 --> 00:30:33,172
- yellow-tinted vision...
- Gary's symptoms.

593
00:30:33,172 --> 00:30:36,951
And fainting. / Maybe why 
Greg dropped in the street.

594
00:30:36,951 --> 00:30:38,720
Guess who's in 
the emergency room.

595
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,221
Who?

596
00:30:40,221 --> 00:30:41,685
Mel davis.

597
00:30:41,685 --> 00:30:43,737
Exact same symptoms as Greg.

598
00:30:50,914 --> 00:30:54,361
We found digoxin in his system.

599
00:30:54,625 --> 00:30:58,240
